Recently, my team has run into an issue where the Phoenix Tuner X application cannot detect any CAN devices on our robot. We’ve done our best to troubleshoot and tried our best to identify the problem but to no avail. Here’s a list of what we’ve done:

  1. Reverted Labview back to 2024 edition (and tried 2025 edition as well)

  2. Restarted robot code several times

  3. Made sure all CANbuses are connected

  4. Ran diagnosis and restarted but didn’t work

  5. The “Advanced FRC” menu in settings provides the option to restart or reinstall Labview, but to our knowledge after several attempts it does not affect the situation.

This affected our Labview build process as well, causing us to not be able to build our code into the robot.

Are there teams who’ve also encountered this problem? If so, is it solved? Thanks for reading, appreciate your feedback and I’ll reply as soon as I can.

Update:
Problem semi solved, but we relied on an older Phoenix Tuner X version (25.1.0). Our Phoenix Tuner X couldn’t install Labview IPK into roborio, causing us to be unable to upload robot code. Even with version 25.1.0 it took us five tries with both laptops. Anyone with same problem?
